that it deserves.

01:03:10.637 --> 01:03:12.070
Right.

01:03:12.103 --> 01:03:15.470
But news, that's something that
somebody wants to suppress.

01:03:15.504 --> 01:03:18.271
Do you remember Kelly Jamerson?

01:03:18.303 --> 01:03:20.037
Yeah. What about him?

01:03:20.071 --> 01:03:22.337
You're gonna love this.

01:03:22.370 --> 01:03:26.171
- 15 MARCH, 1995
MIRACLE MILE
- ♪ Safe to drive... ♪

01:03:26.971 --> 01:03:29.338
POOLE: He was one of
the Rollin 60's Crips

01:03:29.370 --> 01:03:31.538
who attended
a Death Row afterparty.

01:03:32.905 --> 01:03:35.804
Well, he starts throwing up
gang signs, right?

01:03:35.837 --> 01:03:39.170
So Suge's guys decided
to beat him down a little.

01:03:39.204 --> 01:03:42.972
(SHOUTING)

01:03:44.270 --> 01:03:46.471
POOLE: But they beat him
to death.

01:03:46.504 --> 01:03:50.672
This is the section
on the Kelly Jamerson murder.

01:03:50.704 --> 01:03:52.438
However...

01:03:53.571 --> 01:03:55.538
..he's not in here.

01:03:58.238 --> 01:04:02.105
They redacted the entire
incident. He's not in here.

01:04:03.171 --> 01:04:04.839
(GLASS SHATTERS)

01:04:09.037 --> 01:04:11.638
The security guards
who stood by

01:04:11.671 --> 01:04:13.839
and watched a man
being murdered

01:04:13.871 --> 01:04:16.905
were off-duty LAPD officers.

01:04:18.437 --> 01:04:20.638
DARIUS: You redact
the Jamerson incident,

01:04:20.671 --> 01:04:24.270
then you redact the proof
that the LAPD

01:04:24.304 --> 01:04:28.105
has a history of its officers
working for Death Row.

01:04:30.438 --> 01:04:33.371
- Where you goin'?
- Got to follow through.

01:04:33.404 --> 01:04:35.871
You can't just leave.
I just brought up 90 boxes.

01:04:35.904 --> 01:04:37.937
Hey, give me some grace
on this, alright?

01:04:37.970 --> 01:04:41.371
Grace? Fuck does that mean?

01:04:43.671 --> 01:04:47.038
- (GENERAL CHATTER)
- (CUTLERY CLINKS)

01:04:52.104 --> 01:04:55.305
He says, very indignantly,
"I'm the Pope."

01:04:55.337 --> 01:04:56.771
(OTHERS LAUGH)

01:04:56.805 --> 01:04:58.404
DARIUS: You're so full
of shit, Edwards.

01:04:58.437 --> 01:05:00.938
- Excuse me, gentlemen.
- I'm not here to talk to you.

01:05:01.738 --> 01:05:03.504
Commander...

01:05:05.004 --> 01:05:09.271
..I wonder if you could answer
some questions on the record.

01:05:09.303 --> 01:05:11.170
Fasulo, this is Jackson.

01:05:11.203 --> 01:05:13.138
Jackson, Fasulo.

01:05:14.671 --> 01:05:16.571
I've seen
the Wallace murder book.

01:05:16.604 --> 01:05:17.970
Oh, Christ.

01:05:18.004 --> 01:05:19.971
Why did you redact
the past instances

01:05:20.004 --> 01:05:23.604
of the LAPD's connection
with Death Row Records?

01:05:23.637 --> 01:05:27.103
Look, I can't comment
on an open investigation, OK?

01:05:27.136 --> 01:05:29.337
- It's an open investigation?
- Yeah.

01:05:29.370 --> 01:05:31.270
Wow.

01:05:31.304 --> 01:05:32.938
You have any suspects?

01:05:32.971 --> 01:05:35.038
Jackson, I'm not
gonna repeat myself.

01:05:35.070 --> 01:05:37.337
I cannot comment
on an open investigation.

01:05:37.371 --> 01:05:38.572
What's going on here?

01:05:38.605 --> 01:05:41.505
Jackson's been spending
a little bit of time with Poole.

01:05:41.537 --> 01:05:42.937
- Russell. Russell.
- Oh, Poole.

01:05:42.970 --> 01:05:44.970
This is the... OK, alright.

01:05:45.004 --> 01:05:48.671
You know, you are as much
an embarrassment to Edwards

01:05:48.704 --> 01:05:50.338
as Poole was to the LAPD.

01:05:50.371 --> 01:05:56.270
Let me guess, Kevin Gaines
drove David Mack's Impala

01:05:56.303 --> 01:05:57.704
up the grassy knoll,

01:05:57.737 --> 01:05:59.204
where they proceeded
to both whack Kennedy.

01:05:59.238 --> 01:06:01.071
Is that what
you're going for here?

01:06:01.104 --> 01:06:04.204
You find the unsolved murder
of two young men funny?

01:06:04.237 --> 01:06:05.771
No, not at all.

01:06:05.805 --> 01:06:08.371
I find you thinking
that you're spending time

01:06:08.403 --> 01:06:10.537
with the man
who's going to solve this,

01:06:10.570 --> 01:06:12.070
that's what I find funny.

01:06:12.104 --> 01:06:14.838
You want something off
the record, put that thing away.

01:06:14.871 --> 01:06:17.371
- Go on, put it away.
- OK.

01:06:17.403 --> 01:06:19.837
Turn it off, put it away
and I'll tell you something.

01:06:19.871 --> 01:06:21.171
Alright, this is off the record.

01:06:21.204 --> 01:06:25.838
I bet you Poole
hasn't mentioned Wardell Fouse.

01:06:25.871 --> 01:06:28.305
He was a Mob Piru Blood

01:06:28.338 --> 01:06:30.705
that Suge Knight paid
to shoot Biggie.

01:06:30.738 --> 01:06:32.205
Poole tell you that?

01:06:32.238 --> 01:06:35.537
- I'll track him down.
- And bring along a shovel.

01:06:35.570 --> 01:06:38.071
Because he was killed in 2003.

01:06:38.103 --> 01:06:41.571
And listen, Jackson, let me
do you a solid here, OK?

01:06:42.937 --> 01:06:45.738
Poole is certifiable.

01:06:45.770 --> 01:06:47.870
He's a lunatic, alright?

01:06:47.903 --> 01:06:50.937
And if he's giving you
his Captain America routine,

01:06:50.971 --> 01:06:52.538
and the Stars and the Stripes,

01:06:52.571 --> 01:06:55.171
and his... his badge
on his sleeve,

01:06:55.204 --> 01:06:58.105
ask him about his suspension.

01:06:58.903 --> 01:07:00.838
The guy's a disgrace.

01:07:00.870 --> 01:07:03.004
He's a pathological liar.

01:07:03.037 --> 01:07:05.171
I mean, the Wallace's
family civil case

01:07:05.203 --> 01:07:08.070
was based upon his theory
and it was all tossed.

01:07:08.104 --> 01:07:11.438
The man is a lonely shut-in.

01:07:11.471 --> 01:07:14.970
And he needs a warm body
like yourself to talk to.

01:07:15.003 --> 01:07:17.103
So he'll say
whatever you want to hear.

01:07:17.137 --> 01:07:18.737
But reporting things
that aren't true

01:07:18.769 --> 01:07:20.370
is your specialty,
right, Jackson?

01:07:20.404 --> 01:07:21.804
And that's the end of story.

01:07:21.836 --> 01:07:23.404
I don't want to talk
about it anymore,

01:07:23.437 --> 01:07:26.304
and we're about to have dinner,
so maybe you could...

01:07:27.136 --> 01:07:30.237
- Thanks for your time.
- FASULO: Alright.

01:07:32.970 --> 01:07:35.304
Jesus, Mary
and fuckin' Joseph!

01:07:35.338 --> 01:07:36.771
This is your employee?

01:07:36.803 --> 01:07:38.838
Is he medicated? Is he a drunk?

01:07:38.870 --> 01:07:40.870
Why did you even
let him sit down?

01:07:50.437 --> 01:07:54.270
- Yeah, come in.
- Tell me about Wardell Fouse.

01:07:54.303 --> 01:07:55.371
Fouse?

01:07:55.403 --> 01:07:58.304
Oh, you're buying
into that bullshit now?

01:07:59.104 --> 01:08:01.337
Street name was 'Poochie'.

01:08:02.137 --> 01:08:04.671
He was the primary
in the LAPD's current theory.

01:08:04.704 --> 01:08:06.237
- Fuckin' knew this shit?
- I'm a detective.

01:08:06.271 --> 01:08:09.438
A detective says, "I don't know
until I can prove it."

01:08:09.471 --> 01:08:11.971
You've been talkin' about this
dirty cop and that dirty cop.

01:08:12.004 --> 01:08:13.938
Well, what about you, Russ?

01:08:13.971 --> 01:08:17.037
Never a mention about the cop
who got suspended.

01:08:17.071 --> 01:08:18.737
No, let me tell you something.

01:08:18.769 --> 01:08:21.604
You have no idea
what the LAPD is capable of.

01:08:21.638 --> 01:08:23.304
Stop! How can I trust
a single word

01:08:23.337 --> 01:08:25.270
that comes out
of your fuckin' mouth?

01:08:25.304 --> 01:08:26.737
You look at these walls.

01:08:26.770 --> 01:08:28.970
I earned everything here.
Letters of commendation.

01:08:29.004 --> 01:08:31.438
And that's why your son
doesn't talk to you.

01:08:31.470 --> 01:08:33.703
Because you care more
about that than him.

01:08:33.736 --> 01:08:35.804
How fuckin' dare you?

01:08:35.836 --> 01:08:39.870
('BIG POPPA'
BY THE NOTORIOUS B.I.G.)

01:08:39.904 --> 01:08:41.205
SONG: ♪ Oh

01:08:41.237 --> 01:08:44.103
♪ To all the ladies in the place
with style and grace

01:08:44.136 --> 01:08:47.837
♪ Allow me to lace these lyrical
douches in your bushes... ♪

01:08:47.870 --> 01:08:50.304
(SIREN BLARES)

01:08:50.337 --> 01:08:53.572
♪ The back of the club, sippin'
Moët is where you'll find me

01:08:53.604 --> 01:08:56.305
♪ Back of the club,
sippin' Moët... Moët... ♪

01:08:58.069 --> 01:09:00.404
(INDISTINCT
POLICE RADIO CHATTER)

01:09:01.837 --> 01:09:04.438
♪ Straight up, honey,
really I'm askin'

01:09:04.470 --> 01:09:05.837
♪ Most of these niggaz think

01:09:05.870 --> 01:09:07.572
♪ They be mackin'
but they be actin'

01:09:07.604 --> 01:09:09.136
♪ Who they attractin'
with that line

01:09:09.170 --> 01:09:10.871
♪ "What's your name,
what's your sign"? ♪

01:09:10.904 --> 01:09:12.837
OFFICER: Roll down the window.

01:09:13.638 --> 01:09:16.337
Licence and registration.

01:09:19.069 --> 01:09:22.069
- What did I do?
- Licence and registration.

01:09:23.303 --> 01:09:25.304
This is bullshit.

01:09:27.303 --> 01:09:30.837
Sir, are you recording me
right now on that phone?

01:09:30.870 --> 01:09:32.370
- Sir...
- How does that feel to you?

01:09:32.404 --> 01:09:34.671
- Turn off the phone.
- I'm a journalist.

01:09:34.703 --> 01:09:37.337
I got First Amendment rights
and I ain't turnin' off shit.

01:09:37.370 --> 01:09:39.071
Turn off the fuckin' phone,
I said.

01:09:39.104 --> 01:09:41.636
- Let's go. Out of the vehicle.
- What the fuck, man?

01:09:41.669 --> 01:09:43.470
I ain't gettin' out
nowhere, man.

01:09:43.502 --> 01:09:45.437
Get out of the vehicle now.

01:09:45.470 --> 01:09:47.604
Nice and slow.

01:09:47.636 --> 01:09:50.136
Out of the vehicle, now!

01:09:50.170 --> 01:09:53.138
- (SHOUTS) Everybody! Everybody!
- Turn around!

01:09:53.170 --> 01:09:55.804
They fuckin' with me.
I ain't done shit!

01:09:55.837 --> 01:09:57.438
Turn around.

01:09:57.470 --> 01:10:01.337
(DARK, GRIM MUSIC)

01:10:06.438 --> 01:10:10.172
(LOW, PENSIVE MUSIC)

01:10:26.636 --> 01:10:28.304
It's me.

01:10:29.637 --> 01:10:32.105
I'm in the, er...

01:10:33.470 --> 01:10:35.404
..L.A. Central.

01:10:38.370 --> 01:10:41.004
(SIGHS AND MUMBLES)

01:10:44.338 --> 01:10:46.871
BELSHER: Jack?

01:10:51.036 --> 01:10:52.003
Jack?

01:10:52.036 --> 01:10:53.538
I hate to tell you this,

01:10:53.569 --> 01:10:56.171
but Edwards took you
off the Biggie retrospective.

01:10:58.370 --> 01:11:01.172
(LIFT BELL DINGS)

01:11:05.137 --> 01:11:08.838
(DETERMINED
ELECTRIC GUITAR RIFF)

01:11:08.871 --> 01:11:11.737
- EDWARDS: ..of facts.
- I need a word.

01:11:11.769 --> 01:11:15.570
You commissioned
a 20-year retrospective

01:11:15.604 --> 01:11:16.770
and I'm not on it?

01:11:16.804 --> 01:11:18.637
The central claim
has been discredited.

01:11:18.669 --> 01:11:22.137
- According to who?
- The LAPD.

01:11:22.970 --> 01:11:25.305
Of course it was discredited
by them.

01:11:25.337 --> 01:11:27.904
They couldn't solve the case
in the first goddamn place.

01:11:27.937 --> 01:11:31.438
We are distancing ourselves
from the story.

01:11:35.438 --> 01:11:39.137
(BROODING ELECTRIC GUITAR MUSIC)

01:11:47.136 --> 01:11:49.104
(PANTS)

01:11:54.637 --> 01:11:58.038
- DARIUS: Detective Miller?
- MILLER: Who wants to know?

01:12:00.037 --> 01:12:03.338
March 1997, you were the, er...

01:12:03.370 --> 01:12:06.803
..the lead detective on the
Christopher Wallace case, right?

01:12:06.836 --> 01:12:09.172
What are you?
A lawyer? Or a cop?

01:12:09.970 --> 01:12:12.503
- Journalist.
- Even worse.

01:12:13.370 --> 01:12:17.204
I had one foot in retirement.
I don't remember much.

01:12:19.703 --> 01:12:21.937
Too many damn suspects.

01:12:21.971 --> 01:12:23.571
Too many damn leads.

01:12:23.604 --> 01:12:26.471
Was Amir Muhammad one of them?

01:12:28.636 --> 01:12:30.105
What the... (SCOFFS)

01:12:31.404 --> 01:12:34.870
Amir Muhammad
was a possible shooter, yeah.

01:12:34.904 --> 01:12:37.137
But we never interviewed him.

01:12:38.904 --> 01:12:40.871
Can I buy you a beer?

01:12:41.903 --> 01:12:45.171
Everybody had a shooter.
Everybody had a theory.

01:12:45.203 --> 01:12:47.271
My partner asked
onto the case at the time

01:12:47.304 --> 01:12:49.504
because he had a theory.

01:12:49.537 --> 01:12:51.737
Was he... was he
a good detective?

01:12:51.769 --> 01:12:54.671
Was he a good partner?

01:12:54.703 --> 01:12:57.170
MILLER: Russell Poole.

01:12:57.204 --> 01:12:59.305
One of the best.

01:12:59.337 --> 01:13:01.204
(BAT STRIKES BALL)

01:13:03.970 --> 01:13:07.436
Younger guy, but from an older
school than even I was from.

01:13:12.804 --> 01:13:14.670
Worked an honest shift.

01:13:14.704 --> 01:13:16.171
Er, lacked nuance.

01:13:16.204 --> 01:13:19.504
Followed orders to the point
of insubordination.

01:13:19.536 --> 01:13:22.371
Yeah, well, if the cops
can be bending the rules,

01:13:22.402 --> 01:13:24.570
then where does that leave
the rest of us?

01:13:24.604 --> 01:13:27.004
Oh, Christ. That sounds
like something he would say.

01:13:27.036 --> 01:13:29.436
- You sure you haven't met him?
- No.

01:13:30.337 --> 01:13:32.271
MILLER: You gotta be able
to separate yourself

01:13:32.304 --> 01:13:34.038
from the community
that you serve,

01:13:34.070 --> 01:13:36.937
and Poole wasn't cut
from that cloth.

01:13:36.971 --> 01:13:38.770
You know what became of him?

01:13:38.804 --> 01:13:40.838
No idea. They split us up.

01:13:40.870 --> 01:13:44.304
There was a cop. Dirty cop.

01:13:44.337 --> 01:13:47.470
Er, fuck, I can't
remember his name.

01:13:47.502 --> 01:13:49.270
- Bank robber.
- Hmm.

01:13:49.304 --> 01:13:53.171
One theory was that
his loyalty lied with Death Row

01:13:53.203 --> 01:13:55.404
and he was involved
in Biggie's murder,

01:13:55.436 --> 01:13:58.570
so the brass put Poole in charge
of an STF looking into that.

01:13:58.603 --> 01:14:00.170
Huh?

01:14:00.204 --> 01:14:04.370
They gave Poole a special task
force to look into David Mack?

01:14:04.403 --> 01:14:05.871
That's the fuck's name!

01:14:05.904 --> 01:14:08.271
David fuckin' Mack. Yes.

01:14:08.303 --> 01:14:10.803
DARIUS: Thanks for your time.
Appreciate it.

01:14:10.836 --> 01:14:12.570
MILLER: Sure.

01:14:12.603 --> 01:14:14.837
Hey, one more thing.

01:14:16.270 --> 01:14:18.737
You know,
something always struck me

01:14:18.770 --> 01:14:20.571
about that fuck David Mack.

01:14:21.370 --> 01:14:25.737
The whole time he was in prison,
he only got one visitor.

01:14:25.769 --> 01:14:28.204
Amir Muhammad.

01:14:32.836 --> 01:14:37.004
(LOW, EERIE MUSIC)

01:14:45.703 --> 01:14:47.670
(CROWD CHEERS AND SHOUTS)

01:14:47.704 --> 01:14:49.370
ANNOUNCER: <i>No run.</i>

01:14:53.403 --> 01:14:56.970
Aha. Got a question for you.

01:14:57.004 --> 01:15:01.670
Why does the LAPD give
a substandard officer

01:15:01.704 --> 01:15:03.938
his own special task force?

01:15:03.971 --> 01:15:05.771
You don't get to come here.

01:15:05.803 --> 01:15:07.436
It's a free country.

01:15:09.437 --> 01:15:12.436
Then do me a favour -
root for the other team.

01:15:14.736 --> 01:15:17.603
(CROWD CHEERS AND APPLAUDS)

01:15:17.636 --> 01:15:21.369
Substandard? No, sir.

01:15:21.403 --> 01:15:23.537
Are you?

01:15:24.536 --> 01:15:26.604
Unfortunately.

01:15:26.636 --> 01:15:28.670
Alright, everybody, listen up.

01:15:28.704 --> 01:15:31.070
This task force
is changing direction.

01:15:31.104 --> 01:15:33.838
Russ, we got a live one.
We need you to shift focus.

01:15:33.870 --> 01:15:36.004
We're on a live one
right now, sir.

01:15:36.037 --> 01:15:38.871
Let me see you for a second.

01:15:40.737 --> 01:15:42.370
Drop the Death Row pursuit.

01:15:42.403 --> 01:15:45.571
We got cocaine in evidence,
turns out to be Bisquick.

01:15:45.603 --> 01:15:47.970
Same cop signed out
every package.

01:15:48.003 --> 01:15:50.071
Probably selling it
in the street.

01:15:50.103 --> 01:15:53.103
Looks like it's Frank Lyga.

01:15:53.136 --> 01:15:55.270
FRANK: Fuckin' shittin' me, man?

01:15:55.302 --> 01:15:57.403
I'm on unpaid leave

01:15:57.436 --> 01:15:59.303
and you think
I'm going to Evidence Control

01:15:59.337 --> 01:16:02.804
to sign my name to six pounds
of coke I intend to steal?

01:16:02.836 --> 01:16:05.403
Come on, bro!

01:16:06.502 --> 01:16:08.171
DARIUS: Did you believe him?

01:16:09.170 --> 01:16:10.237
Yeah.

01:16:11.403 --> 01:16:12.938
Yeah, I did.

01:16:12.970 --> 01:16:14.938
His incident with Gaines

01:16:14.971 --> 01:16:19.004
drove a very strong racial wedge
through the force.

01:16:19.037 --> 01:16:20.304
There's your duffel.

01:16:20.336 --> 01:16:22.603
Did you not want
to see my ID or...?

01:16:22.637 --> 01:16:24.604
I'm sure you ain't
gonna rob the place.

01:16:24.636 --> 01:16:26.803
POOLE: Evidence Control
was so lax,

01:16:26.837 --> 01:16:30.205
Detective Lyga was
the easiest target in the world

01:16:30.236 --> 01:16:32.336
for anybody who wanted
to frame him.

01:16:32.369 --> 01:16:34.071
(OFFICER CHUCKLES)

01:16:34.104 --> 01:16:35.604
Detective!

01:16:35.637 --> 01:16:38.804
You left your evidence bag.

01:16:38.836 --> 01:16:41.038
I have to get back
to Disneyland.

01:16:42.136 --> 01:16:43.736
What, you...

01:16:43.769 --> 01:16:46.038
(SIGHS)

01:16:51.470 --> 01:16:55.704
POOLE: I didn't know who
to trust, so I went to the top.

01:16:55.737 --> 01:16:57.237
Chief?

01:16:57.270 --> 01:17:01.138
- Go away, Poole.
- You'd like that, wouldn't you?

01:17:01.170 --> 01:17:03.469
Sir, this department
has bad elements.

01:17:03.502 --> 01:17:06.137
Now, I can't tell you
who killed Christopher Wallace

01:17:06.170 --> 01:17:08.269
because I've not been allowed
to do my job properly.

01:17:08.302 --> 01:17:11.469
Every time I turn a corner,
I'm not allowed to look.

01:17:11.503 --> 01:17:14.470
Why? Because my suspects
are cops.

01:17:14.503 --> 01:17:16.870
We've all sworn the same oath

01:17:16.904 --> 01:17:19.903
to uphold the law
regardless of the circumstances.

01:17:19.937 --> 01:17:22.871
I believe we owe that
to Christopher Wallace,

01:17:22.903 --> 01:17:26.436
to his mother
and to his family.

